[XGLocalizedData]
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Элитные виды противников получают дополнительное действие, когда им наносится урон."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Есть множество видов криссалидов: от хилого Ползуна до гигантского Отродья."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Удавы намного крепче обыкновенных Гадюк. Они дерутся только врукопашную и не отпускают жертву почти до самой смерти."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Мамбы используют Стреломёт и Общий Вид. У них есть уникальная способность добивать раненых бойцов. Mambas use a Boltcaster with Squadsight. They have a unique ability to finish off wounded soldiers."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Виверна, уникальная разновидность Гадюки, может плеваться огнём и воспламенять большие территории."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Sectoid Soldier has poor psi abilities, but makes up for it with combat training."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Sectoid Mindbenders have above average psi abilities that break the will of even the strongest soldiers."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Puppeteer has the ability to raise the dead over and over again."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Firestarters are Berserkers that breathe fire. Like a dragon. Yeah."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Muton Pyros have Dragonrounds. Even graze shots from them end up dealing a lot of damage."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="When you get hit by a Muton Infector, their Venom rounds will add insult to injury."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Muton Captains use Light Em Up to spew a lot of bullets at their enemies."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Muton Captains and Champions have a Warcry that bolsters all the allies around."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Muton Champion can react to enemy fire with verious defensive options, among them a personal shield."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Muton Primes not only come with a plasma cannon, but they also use Light Em Up and Personal Shield."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Shoggoth is a Faceless that hides among Advent Troopers. You can start feeling paranoid now."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Sectoid Soldiers don't get extra damage from sword attacks like other Sectoids."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="There are three known Sectoid variations: Soldier, Mindbender, Puppeteer"
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Viper comes with three variants: Boa, Mamba, Wyvern."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Muton has a range of variants: Pyro, Infector, Captain, Champion, Prime"
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Prime versions exist for all aliens. There is also a Sectopod Prime. Be very afraid."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="There are three Archon variants: Torcher, Executioner, Sentinel."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Archon Torcher uses Devastate instead of Blazing Pinions. He will even use it on reveal."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Archon Valkyries only attack in melee, but drains the enemies lifeforce with every hit."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Sentinel Archons use Overwatch with Guardian and Covering Fire on reveal and on most other occasions."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="If you can read this, you don't need glasses."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Tech Commandos don't have a shield generator, but they use a Gremlin." 
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Tech Commandos can detonate explosives that your soldiers carry."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The offensive version of the Shieldbearer is called a Breacher. He has a shotgun."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Between stunlance and shotgun, the Assault has everything it needs to dominate close quarters combat."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Trauma Lancers use a taser pistol that can impair soldiers at range."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="AutoDocs increase the effeciency of all ADVENT around them by spreading heals around with a Gremlin drone."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="A walking war crime, the Hazard MEC only get deployed once ADVENT starts to get desperate."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Anti-Riot MEC supports its squad with smoke and uses cluster flashbangs against its enemies."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Sectopod Prime is the pinnacle of ADVENT engineering. Be prepared." 
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Thanks to its Annihilation protocol AI, Sectopod Primes have enough firepower to wipe out an ill-prepared squad."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Drones are small autonomous scouts. After finding enemies, they support ADVENT squads with its melee stunner."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="There are four tiers of ADVENT Sergeants: ADVENT, Advanced, Elite and Exalted."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="There are 8 types of Chryssalid: Crawler, Drone, Hunter, Hunterkiller, Spitter, King, Queen, Abomination."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Chryssalid appear everywhere, even outside of retaliations. So do Berserkers."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Chryssalid Spitters can fire a poisonous projectile at their enemies and melee attack in the same turn."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Chryssalid King is physically imposing and should not be engaged in close combat."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Queen is the heart of the Chryssalid swarm. They constantly breed more members for the nest, even in battle."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Born from genetic defects, the Chryssalid Abomination is insanely large. Like ... really, really big."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Intrusion Countermeasure(ICE) is a Codex that takes down key opponents with a Boltcaster."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="When ADVENT needs to respond to emergencies fast, they can teleport in with an ADVENT Codex."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="The Codex Splitter patrols on his own, but once engaged, he will quickly chain-split into multiples."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Codex Bombers use their Psi Bomb ability on reveal. Engage carefully."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="There are four types of Codex: ICE, ADVENT, Bomber, Splitter."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="There are seven different ADVENT Troopers: Heavy, Gunslinger, Demolitionist, Sentinel, Wrecker, Striker, Gatling Trooper."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Heavy ADVENT Troopers have some extra armor."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Gunslingers carry a light pistol that they can use with Faceoff and Lightning Hands."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Experienced Demolitionists gain access to plasma grenades, grenade launchers and even rocket launchers."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Sentinels are Overwatch specialists. Their Tactical Fire ability lets them shoot and overwatch in one turn."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Wreckers have ammo that pierces and shreds armor. They also deal extra damage to environmental objects, so maybe don't hide behind that car..."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="Strikers have shotguns and increased mobility, high ranked Strikers also gain Close Combat Specialist."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="A fully ranked Gatling Trooper has Demolition, Light Em Up and Chain Shot."
+GameplayTips_Tactical="In A Better ADVENT, the only thing that changes about enemies with difficulty is their health. Everything else is fixed."
